  "response_text": "A silver-blue sporty Mazda coupe drives along a wet-looking mountain road at dusk, seen from behind and slightly to the side. It has a low, wedge-like body, a sloping rear window, and a broad rear bumper. Metal guardrails run along the road, with dark hills and bare trees silhouetted against a bluish-purple sky. The car moves steadily through the lane, its body reflecting the cool light from the sky.\n\nAs the car continues along the winding road, another silver-blue Mazda appears alongside and then becomes the main focus. This second car is a more upright, boxy late-1970s sedan or coupe, with a squared-off front grille, rectangular headlights, chrome trim, and small steel wheels. The two cars travel in sequence on the same curving mountain highway, one following the other. Large white on-screen numbers, “25/34,” appear near the lower left, with smaller fine print beside them that is difficult to read, suggesting fuel-economy information. The road curves through wooded hills, and the cars remain framed against guardrails, dark slopes, and distant mountains.\n\nThe view shifts to the silver Mazda traveling near a coastline. The road bends along a high overlook, with water and small landforms visible beyond the guardrail. One car passes out of view to the left while the other continues around the curve, approaching head-on. The vehicle’s front end is clearly shown: a black rectangular grille, chrome bumper accents, and square headlights. The large “25/34” fuel-economy text remains at the bottom of the image during these driving scenes, with small explanatory text beside it.\n\nInside the car, a close view shows a driver’s right hand gripping a manual gearshift knob. The hand appears adult, light-skinned, wearing a wristwatch and a long-sleeved jacket or shirt. The round top of the shift knob shows a shift-pattern diagram, reinforcing that this is a manual transmission. The hand rests firmly on the gear lever beside the dark center console and dashboard controls.\n\nThe exterior driving view returns briefly, showing the silver Mazda from a low front-side angle as it moves along the road under a cloudy purple sky. The driver’s side window area is visible, though the driver’s face is not clear.\n\nBack inside, the dashboard is shown in close-up. The center area has rectangular air vents above a dark audio/control panel. A hand reaches in from the left and adjusts the stereo or radio controls, pressing or turning a small control on the front panel. The dashboard is mostly black, with chrome or silver trim outlining the vents.\n\nAnother interior view demonstrates the rear-seat/cargo area. The rear seat appears folded down, creating a longer flat space from the trunk or rear compartment into the cabin. A long object, possibly a folding tripod or similar gear with thin metal legs, is placed or slid into the extended cargo area, showing how the space can carry longer items.\n\nNear the end, the two silver Mazda 626 models are parked side by side on a scenic overlook at sunset. The ocean or a large body of water stretches behind them, with dark headlands and islands silhouetted against a pink and purple sky. Large white price text appears above the cars: “Sedan $5495” and “Coupe $5795,” with smaller lines of fine print to the right that are not fully legible. The final view leaves the two cars parked together in the foreground, angled slightly toward the viewer, with the calm coastal landscape and fading evening light behind them.",
